      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: preserve partial JUnit results",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- preserve summaries from valid JUnit files when sibling reports are malformed or partial, while emitting named warnings\n- auto-discover complete reports up to 16 MiB each and 64 MiB total instead of silently truncating at 1 MiB; warn explicitly when a bound is exceeded\n- add opt-in `--fail-on-test-failures`, `results.failOnFailures`, and `CRABBOX_RESULTS_FAIL_ON_FAILURES` policy without replacing existing command failures\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/480\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `node scripts/build-docs-site.mjs`\n- focused JUnit/config/run tests\n- structured autoreview: clean on the first pass\n\n## Live proof\n\nBuilt the final CLI and ran three real `local-container` Docker leases with automatic cleanup:\n\n1. Explicit `good.xml,bad.xml,large.xml`, where the command exited 0, `bad.xml` was partial, `large.xml` was 2 MiB, and `good.xml` contained one failure. Crabbox preserved two valid files, warned by name for `bad.xml`, recorded two tests/one failure, and changed the final exit to 1 only because `--fail-on-test-failures` was enabled.\n2. `--results-auto` with a valid 2 MiB report plus a partial report. Crabbox preserved the complete large report, warned for the partial file, recorded one passing test, and exited 0.\n3. `--results-auto` with a report above 16 MiB. Crabbox emitted `report exceeds 16777216-byte per-file limit` with the file name and exited 0; the report was not silently truncated.\n4. A zero-exit command wrote a failing testcase while omitting aggregate failure/error attributes. Crabbox derived `failures=1`, printed the failed case, and exited 1 under the opt-in policy.\n\nAll three containers were released and absent afterward. No remote provider or paid resource was used.\n",
